Rating: 4
This meat loaf was quick and delicious. Due to ingredients on hand, I substituted meat loaf combo (veal, pork, beef), and dried cherries (chopped in food processor with the shallots) and dried blueberries. Because of the pork in my mix, I baked it to 185 degrees. I used peach spread for glaze mixed with Dijon mustard with horseradish. I will definitely make this again. A wonderful change from the usual ketchup'd meat loaf!

Rating: 4
Just want to add my two cents. I have always enjoyed a good meatloaf and this is one of my favorites. I usually follow the recipe with one exception. A few times I have subsituted the Apricot preserves with some homemade peach jam that my mother makes. Other than that, this recipe is dead on.

