Very fast and surprisingly delicious for meatloaf. Not the greasy falling apart meatloaf w/ketchup that I remembered. Feed it w/confidence to meatloaf sceptics!

Rating: 4
Me and my extremely beautiful girlfriend made this meatloaf one night and it was by far the best meatloaf I've ever had. We did, of course, make a few alterations. We added some sausage and used diced fresh apples instead of dried fruit. We had a little more than would fit in the dish we cooked it in, so we made a couple of burger-like patties out of it and baked it on a sheet next to the loaf (they took a lot less time to cook, of course). The mustard/apricot preserve topping was amazing (especially on the patties, where it was much more prevalent) and we've begun using it on other meat as well.

